Post Graduate courses


In addition to the B.E. courses, the college offers two year Master of Technology courses in four disciplines, MBA and MCA. All of the following courses are affiliated with the Visvesvaraya Technological University.33

Master of Business Administration (MBA)
Master of Computer Applications (MCA)
Master of Technology in Biotechnology
Master of Technology in Computer Science and Engineering
Master of Technology in Digital Communication Engineering
Master of Technology in Machine Design


Architecture


Acharya's NRV School of Architecture (ASA) offers a five year undergraduate course in architecture (B.Arch), which is accredited by the Council of Architecture (COA).3435
Faculty
AIT maintains a Teacher-student ratio of 1:10.36
It is the first college in Karnataka to put in effect the Sixth Central Pay Commission recommendations for faculty pay scale.37
Research Centers
The Visvesvaraya Technological University has recognised four departments of AIT as Research Centers.3839
The Institute receives MODROBS grant from AICTE for research activities and upgraded state of art lab facilities.40
The following departments of the college are recognised as Research Centers: 4142

Department of Bio-technology


Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering


Department of Mathematics


Department of Mechanical Engineering

Accredition and Rankings

AIT is one of the few colleges in Karnataka to be accredited by the National Board of Accreditation (NBA).43 It was the first college under the Visvesvaraya Technological University to start an undergraduate course in Mechatronics Engineering in Karnataka.44 It is one of the seven colleges in Karnataka to be funded by the World Bank and is granted endowments by the Visvesvaraya Technological University to carry out research works in both its undergraduate and postgraduate departments.4546
The college is ranked consistently among the top 50 Engineering colleges in India by publications and organizations namely Outlook India,4748 Data Quest,495051 NASSCOM and Silicon India,52 EFY,53 CSR-GHRDC5455 and CSR.56 AIT was ranked among the top 5 Engineering colleges in Karnataka by the Global Human Resources Development Centre(GHRDC).57 It was also bestowed South India's Excellent Institution Award by A-Plus TV Media Works.58
AIT features as an A+ institution in the rankings of the publication Career 360.59
Administration
Governing council
The governing council of the college consists of 11 members. The body comprises five members from the JMJ Education Society, one staff representative, one University Grants Commission member, one AICTE nominee, one state government, Dept. of Technical Education nominee, one university nominee, and one Member Secretary, the principal.6061
Academic council
The academic council of the college is headed by the principal. Student enrollments, academics, assessments, examinations are managed by the respective deans, controller of examinations and appointed faculty members. The college administration is managed by the director of administration. The research department is headed by the director of R&amp;D. The placement department is managed by the principal, director of HR and one expert in the subject. Each academic department is headed by respective heads of departments (HoDs).6263
Proctorial system
Faculty members are appointed as proctors for the students of their respective departments to monitor their attendance, performance in tests, co-curricular activities and personality development. Each proctor supervises 20 students in an academic semester.6465
Campus

AIT Stadium


Educational facilities


The college has a Central Library with EDUSAT programmes, E-learning facilities and Online Public Access Catalog (OPAC) gateway.66
The institution has various has collaborations with Multinational Corporations and has established various learning facilities like Vasundhara Industrial Automation Learning Center,67 IBM Software Center of Excellence,68 Microsoft IT Academy,69 and Novell Centre of Excellence.70
International Academy for Competency Enhancement (IACE), the Finishing School of Acharya Institutes provides soft skills and technical trainings to students.71

Entrepreneur Incubation Cell


The college and signed an Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with IBM and has established IBM Entrepreneur Incubation Center in the campus.7273

Infrastructure


The college provides a 24/7 campus Wi-Fi access.74 The college has an Auditorium with a capacity of 500+ seats, Board rooms, Conference and Seminar Halls. The institution has its own multipurpose stadium known as the Smt. Nagarathnama Stadium with a capacity of over 10,000 people.75 The college also has a National Technical Manpower Information System (NTMIS)76 and 24/7 ATM center/outlet operated by Axis Bank. The college operates a Campus clinic which provides medical facilities to the students.

Environmental Initiatives


The institution has built its own sewage treatment plant in the campus and has employed methods for rain water harvesting. The campus also boasts of a four-acre artificial lake.77

Hostels and Canteens


AIT provides Hostel Accommodation for both boys and girls. The Hostel Mess serves North Indian, South Indian and Chinese cuisine. The college has separate Food Court, Cafeteria and Canteen which serve vegetarian food in the campus. The campus also houses a Coffee Day Xpress operated by the Coffee Day.78

Recreational Facilities


The college has a Student activity center which provides indoor games and gymnasium facilities. The institution also organises horse riding and yoga learning camps on campus for the students.7980
Industry interaction

IBM Entrepreneur Incubation Center

The college has industry collaborations and has signed Memorandum of Understanding (MoUs) with Computer Society of India (CSI), Environ Software Pvt Ltd, IBM, Infosys, ISTE, Keane, Microsoft, Novell, Oracle, SAP Labs, Sun Microsystems, United Technologies, Vasundhara Automation and Engineering Services Pvt. Ltd. (VAES), VMware, Wipro and many other leading companies to increase the industry interaction.81828384
University twinning programs
AIT has twinning programs with foreign universities for student exchange programme and higher studies. Some of them are Jiujiang University, Shandong University, Ocean University of China and Hefei University in China; Old Dominion University in USA; Thames Valley University in UK; Andalusia Technology Park in Spain; L&lt;U+00FC&gt;beck University of Applied Sciences in Germany.85
The college also has tie-ups with Mysore University, Mysore and Indian Institute of Technology, Bombay (IIT-B) in India.86
Cultural activities

 Singer Benny Dayal performing in Acharya Habba 2011


Acharya Habba


The college organises an annual inter-collegiate culfest known as the &quot;Acharya Habba&quot; which sees a crowd of over 30000 students from over 300 colleges across Karnataka.878889

Ethnic day


Students dress up in their traditional clothes highlighting the cultural importance of the region they belong to.90

Freshers' day


The Freshers are welcomed by the seniors of various departments of the college in an extravagant and cheerful way. The students of the college organise various cultural, extra-curricular and technical activities to greet and encourage the freshers who have joined the college. Various stalls are organised by different departments and clubs of the college to exhibit the facilities, rules &amp; regulations and achievements of the college.91
