Student projects

Hovercraft


An one-seater hovercraft was designed by a team of Mechanical Engineering students of AIT as their final year project work. The hovercraft measured 8.5 feet in length and runs on a Yezdi Roadking 250cc, 16 bhp, 2-stroke engine powered by Race Engine Technology. The engine can accommodate high load operating conditions and has been designed for low speed operations. The weighing capability of the craft is 260 kilograms. The hovercraft is also equipped with GPS and has been made cost efficient.96

'''Other '''


A mini car and a motor bike have been designed by the students of AIT which is fuel efficient and can run on alternative sources of energy, thereby saving the precious fossil fuels.97
Student counselling and guidance

DH-PV edu-counselling


Annually, AIT in collaboration with Indian Newspaper Deccan Herald and Prajavani, organises a career counselling for students who have just passed their Higher Secondary and Entrance examinations.9899100101

Jnana Degula


The college co-organises an annual educational fair known as the Jnana Degula in the Palace grounds located in Bangalore. The students are guided to make an informed career choice which corresponds to their undergraduate education. The fair attracts various institutions across Karnataka to showcase their colleges and their facilities through stalls.102103
Placements
Placement cell
The training and placement cell helps get students placed in Multinational corporations (MNCs) and Indian Companies. The cell appoints student placement coordinators from every department to manage its activities, which are guided by placement directors.104 The placement cell also organises pool-campus placement drive for government and private colleges located in rural places of Karnataka.105
A few companies which have recruited from the college campus are ABB, Accenture, American Express, Biocon, BOSCH, CISCO, Cognizant Technologies, DELL, Dr. Reddy's Laboratories, Essar, Ford Motors, GE, Google India, Harley Davidson, IBM, Indian Air force, Indian Army, Indian Navy, Infosys, Mahindra &amp; Mahindra, Maruti Suzuki, Mcafee, Michelin, Punj Lloyd, Reliance Industries, Rockwell Automation, Siemens, L &amp; T, Tata Elxsi and Wipro.106
